緬甸[釋放](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/14/myanmar-suu-kyi-is-free-at-
last/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/14/myanmar-suu-kyi-is-free-at-
last/")翁山蘇姬與泰國[紅杉軍抗議](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/thailand-
red-shirt-protests-2010/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/thailand-red-shirt-
protests-2010/")應該是 2010 年東南亞最大的政治事件。但全球之聲也報導了這個地區內其他值得注意的議題。以下是我們的年度總結：

**社群媒體**

2010
年是菲律賓和緬甸的選舉年。社群媒體被有效的裡用來[監督](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/11/monitoring-
philippine-elections-through-social-media/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/11/monitoring-philippine-elections-
through-social-
media/")菲律賓的選舉結果，以及推廣緬甸的[抵制選舉](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/27/myanmar-
boycott-elections-campaign/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/27/myanmar-boycott-elections-
campaign/")運動。

在推特上，菲律賓人九月就送出[聖誕祝福](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/02/philippines-
merry-christmas-is-top-twitter-topic/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/02/philippines-merry-christmas-is-top-
twitter-topic/")。汶萊一起[自殺未遂](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/18/brunei-
suicide-attempt-stirs-online-buzz/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/18/brunei-suicide-attempt-stirs-
online-buzz/")事件也在推特上留下紀錄。#slashing 和 #369
這兩個標籤指的是新加坡一連串的[砍人案件](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/14/singapore-
rising-gang-violence/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/14/singapore-
rising-gang-violence/")。

在馬來西亞，部落格被用來促進國內[團結](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/07/malaysia-
blogging-to-promote-national-unity/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/07/malaysia-blogging-to-promote-
national-unity/")。Borneo Colours
集合了世界第三大島[婆羅洲](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/14/borneo-island-
uniting-bloggers-through-borneo-colours/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/14/borneo-island-uniting-bloggers-
through-borneo-colours/")內的部落格。BruneiTweet
是汶萊的「[國家推特帳號](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/30/bruneis-national-
twitter-account/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/30/bruneis-national-
twitter-account/")」。互動式性教育網站
[sexxie.tv](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/02/southeast-asia-
interactive-sex-education-website/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/02/southeast-asia-interactive-sex-
education-website/") 在新加坡成立，現在也在印尼、菲律賓和印度營運。全球之聲作者 Keta Haluha
報導了在臉書上的[東帝汶名人](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/05/timorese-on-
facebook/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/05/timorese-on-facebook/")。

一段關於東帝汶[警察暴力](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/25/timor-police-
brutality-video/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/25/timor-police-
brutality-
video/")的影片被傳上網路。一名來自菲律賓的家務助理[紀錄](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/03/philippines-
labor-attache-earns-filipino-migrant-communitys-ire/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/03/philippines-labor-attache-earns-
filipino-migrant-communitys-ire/")了香港的菲律賓勞工聯絡人是如何對待陷入困境的工人。索尼公司控告一名叫做
[Sony](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/02/indonesia-sony-versus-sony/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/02/indonesia-sony-versus-sony/")
的部落客網域名稱侵權。泰國的臉書使用者建立了一個批評[國家文化部](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/11/thailand-%E2%80%9Cwere-
sick-of-ministry-of-culture%E2%80%9D/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/11/thailand-“were-sick-of-ministry-of-
culture”/")的頁面。一位越南父親為他失蹤的女兒向網友[求助](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/25/vietnam-
dad-asks-netizens-to-help-find-missing-daughter/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/25/vietnam-dad-asks-netizens-to-help-
find-missing-daughter/")。

全球之聲報導了以下公民媒體活動：新加坡的
[Twestival](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/31/singapore-
twestivalsg-2010/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/31/singapore-
twestivalsg-2010/")，金邊的
[Barcamp](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/05/cambodia-countdown-to-
barcamp-phnom-penh-2010/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/05/cambodia-
countdown-to-barcamp-phnom-penh-2010/")、在仰光舉行的緬甸第一場
[Barcamp](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/01/myanmars-first-barcamp-in-
yangon/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/01/myanmars-first-barcamp-in-
yangon/")、西貢的 [Barcamp 及
Educamp](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/17/vietnam-barcamp-and-
educamp-saigon-2010/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/17/vietnam-
barcamp-and-educamp-saigon-2010/")。

[![Screenshot of Global Voices website being banned in
Myanmar](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gv-access-
denied.jpg)](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/01/gv-
access-denied.jpg)

全球之聲網站在緬甸無法連結的螢幕截圖

**審查制度**

本地區的網路與媒體審查更趨嚴格。在[馬來西亞](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/20/malaysia-
where-is-press-freedom-heading-now/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/20/malaysia-where-is-press-freedom-
heading-now/")、[新加坡](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/22/censorship-in-
singapore/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/22/censorship-in-
singapore/")和[柬埔寨](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/11/cambodia-mixed-
views-on-freedom-of-expression/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/11/cambodia-mixed-views-on-freedom-of-
expression/")，媒體自由和表達意見的自由都是部落客積極討論的議題。

網路自由受到許多法律措施限制，例如柬埔寨的[網路防火牆](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/02/cambodias-
great-internet-firewall/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/02/cambodias-
great-internet-
firewall/")和泰國的[網路偵查](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/24/cyber-scout-
thailand%E2%80%99s-internet-police/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/24/cyber-scout-thailand’s-internet-
police/")程式。緬甸網友抱怨ㄧ有更多[無法連結](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/18/more-
websites-banned-in-myanmar-global-voices-banned-too/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/18/more-websites-banned-in-myanmar-
global-voices-banned-
too/")的網站和部落格，包括全球之聲在內。本地區各國政府用保護青少年道德觀為藉口，封鎖網路上的「[有害](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/16/southeast-
asia-sex-and-web-censorship/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/16/southeast-asia-sex-and-web-
censorship/")」內容。

為了促進媒體自由，菲律賓公民團體推動讓[資訊自由法案](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/09/philippines-
congress-fails-to-pass-freedom-of-information-bill/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/09/philippines-congress-fails-to-pass-
freedom-of-information-
bill/")儘快通過。同時印尼網友反對政府提案的[壓迫性](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/17/sos-
internet-indonesia/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/17/sos-internet-
indonesia/")網路規範。

[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/10/merapi-375x237.jpg)](http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=443121106315&set=a.443120986315.242329.79572061315)

印尼火山爆發的影響，照片來自日惹市官方臉書頁面。

**重大災難**

2010
年是充滿災難的一年。其中死傷最為慘重的是柬埔寨的[送水節](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/23/cambodia-
stampede-tragedy-during-water-festival/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/23/cambodia-stampede-tragedy-during-
water-festival/")[推擠致死事件](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/29/cambodia-
lessons-from-the-water-festival-stampede/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/29/cambodia-lessons-from-the-water-
festival-stampede/")。

印尼在[四十八小時內](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/28/indonesia-earthquake-
tsunami-volcanic-eruption-in-48-hours/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/28/indonesia-earthquake-tsunami-
volcanic-eruption-
in-48-hours/")接連受到地震、海嘯及火山爆發侵襲。印尼[西巴布亞](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/07/indonesia-
west-papua-flashflood/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/07/indonesia-
west-papua-
flashflood/")、新加坡、[泰國](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/21/thailand-
worst-flooding-in-decades/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/21/thailand-worst-flooding-in-
decades/")、越南和馬來西亞[北部數州](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/07/malaysia-
flood-hits-northern-states/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/07/malaysia-flood-hits-northern-
states/")遭逢水患。想像一下新加坡的[購物街](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/08/the-
great-floods-of-singapore/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/08/the-
great-floods-of-
singapore/")被洪水淹沒。[曼谷](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/26/flooding-
disaster-in-thailand/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/26/flooding-
disaster-in-
thailand/")也淹了數星期的水。而菲律賓則在七月經歷了[缺水危機](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/22/philippines-
manila-water-crisis/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/22/philippines-
manila-water-crisis/")。

籠罩新加坡、馬來西亞及印尼的[霾害](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/22/haze-envelops-
singapore/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/22/haze-envelops-
singapore/")以新加坡受害最嚴重。[漏油事件](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/29/oil-
spill-disaster-in-singapore/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/29/oil-
spill-disaster-in-singapore/")也毀掉了新加坡部份海岸區。

網友回報了印尼[蘇門答臘](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/08/indonesia-sumatra-
quake-reporting-with-twitter/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/08/indonesia-sumatra-quake-reporting-
with-
twitter/")地震災情。公民記者也記錄了菲律賓阿爾拜省火山爆發後被迫離家[難民](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/03/philippines-
life-in-evacuation-centers/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/03/philippines-life-in-evacuation-
centers/")的狀況。

[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/bangkok-
skyline.jpg)](http://twitpic.com/1p2rnp)

曼谷大火。照片由 BKKApologist 提供。

**政治**

如前面提到的，泰國紅杉軍示威癱瘓首都[兩個月](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/11/thailand-
bloggers-document-violent-clashes/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/11/thailand-bloggers-document-violent-
clashes/")，可算是 2010 年本地區最重大的政治事件。

上千反政府抗議人士[湧入](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/12/thailand-citizen-
videos-of-violent-clash/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/12/thailand-
citizen-videos-of-violent-
clash/")首都[圍堵](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/16/bangkok-clashes-
pictures-videos-and-twitter-reports/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/16/bangkok-clashes-pictures-videos-
and-twitter-
reports/")政府機關，要求首相下台。這是一次「[血腥](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/16/thailand-%E2%80%9Cbloody%E2%80%9D-tuesday/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/16/thailand-“bloody”-tuesday/")」抗議，因為抗議者將血灑在政府機關建築物及政府官員的住家房屋上。雖然當局實施媒體檢查，抗議者和政府軍的衝突依然被[部落客](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/21/thailand-
blog-reactions-to-bangkok-violence/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/21/thailand-blog-reactions-to-bangkok-
violence/")記錄了下來。

其他的東南亞重要政治事件包括翁山蘇姬的釋放。至少到目前為止，這個行動成功將世界各國的注意力從緬甸軍政府黨派控制的[選舉](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/09/myanmar-
election-junta-backed-party-wins-violence-erupts/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/09/myanmar-election-junta-backed-
party-wins-violence-
erupts/")上轉移開來。順道一提，緬甸現在有了[新國旗和新國名](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/26/myanmars-
new-flag-and-new-name/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/26/myanmars-
new-flag-and-new-name/")。

在赤柬政權垮台超過三十年後，康克由（又稱杜赫同志）終於因反人類罪被赤柬法庭[定罪](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/02/cambodia-
mixed-views-on-duch-verdict/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/02/cambodia-mixed-views-on-duch-
verdict/")，成為全球重大新聞。

同時在寮國，[集束彈藥公約國際會議](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/26/laos-and-the-
convention-on-cluster-munitions/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/26/laos-and-the-convention-on-cluster-
munitions/")突顯出寮國是世界上受到集束彈藥影響最為嚴重的國家。

歐巴馬在印尼的[返鄉](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/11/obamas-indonesian-
homecoming-charms-residents/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/11/obamas-indonesian-homecoming-
charms-
residents/")演講激勵了許多印尼人。另一場被網友熱烈討論的演說則是印尼總統的獨立紀念日[演講](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/18/indonesia-
whats-wrong-mr-president/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/18/indonesia-whats-wrong-mr-
president/")。

馬來西亞與印尼的海上[邊界糾紛](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/06/malaysia-indonesia-
border-row/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/06/malaysia-indonesia-
border-
row/")只是本地區數不清的邊界糾紛之一。九名香港旅客在菲律賓[劫持人質](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/24/philippines-
hostage-drama-ends-in-violence/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/24/philippines-hostage-drama-ends-in-
violence/")事件中喪生，菲律賓為此向香港[道歉](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/28/philippines-%E2%80%9Chong-
kong-our-apology-for-what-happened%E2%80%9D/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/28/philippines-“hong-kong-our-apology-
for-what-happened”/")。

[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/12/pinoyleaks-375x184.png)](http://www.pinoyleaks.org/)

**維基解密**

[維基解密](https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/wikileaks-and-the-world/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/specialcoverage/wikileaks-and-the-
world/")提供了一些本地有趣的政治八卦。新加坡的李光耀形容北韓是被一個「軟弱老人」統治的「[一群神經病](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/02/singapore-
wikileaks-and-the-%E2%80%9Cflabby-old-chap%E2%80%9D-comment/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/02/singapore-wikileaks-and-
the-“flabby-old-
chap”-comment/")」。其他新加坡高級官員也對[鄰國](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/13/wikileaks-
reveals-how-singapore-views-its-neighbors/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/13/wikileaks-reveals-how-singapore-
views-its-
neighbors/")領導人發表了一些不怎麼中聽的評語。不出所料，新加坡政府表示維基解密所透漏的只不過是[茶餘飯後的閒談](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/14/singapore-
dismisses-wikileaks-expose-as-mere-%E2%80%98cocktail-talk%E2%80%99/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/14/singapore-dismisses-wikileaks-
expose-as-mere-‘cocktail-talk’/")，毋需認真看待。

馬來西亞被迫[否認](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/05/malaysia-two-firms-
mentioned-in-wikileaks-documents/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/05/malaysia-two-firms-mentioned-in-
wikileaks-
documents/")向中國購買導彈技術欲轉售給伊朗。泰國洩漏的電訊顯示國際對[維克多．布特一案](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/07/wikileaks-
and-thailand/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/07/wikileaks-and-
thailand/")施加壓力。布特被控為世界最大的軍火走私商。

本地區亦出現了許多[複製](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/28/wikileaks-thaileaks-
indoleaks-pinoyleaks/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/28/wikileaks-
thaileaks-indoleaks-pinoyleaks/")維基解密的網站：泰國解密、印尼解密和菲律賓解密。

**經濟**

馬來西亞在 2010 年啟動了「[新經濟模型](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/02/malaysia-
new-economic-model/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/02/malaysia-new-
economic-model/")」。首相公佈 [2011
年預算](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/17/malaysia-
budget-2011-announced-2/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/17/malaysia-
budget-2011-announced-2/")時引起了部落客的激烈反應，尤其是其中建造新[摩天大樓](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/02/malaysia-
no-to-mega-tower/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/02/malaysia-no-to-
mega-tower/")的計畫。

新加坡因是否該實施[最低工資法](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/28/singapore-minimum-
wage-debate/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/28/singapore-minimum-
wage-
debate/")爆發激烈爭論。印尼的[銀行紓困](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/08/indonesia-
bank-bailout-sparks-political-crisis/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/08/indonesia-bank-bailout-sparks-
political-
crisis/")演變成爭議性的政治事件。寮國和菲律賓發行[新鈔](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/26/philippines-
filipinos-welcome-new-year-with-new-banknotes/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/26/philippines-filipinos-welcome-new-
year-with-new-banknotes/")，但有些批評者並不滿意。

**體育**

全球之聲報導了這個地區的[足球部落格](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/27/southeast-asia-
blogging-about-football/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/27/southeast-
asia-blogging-about-
football/")。東南亞足球錦標賽在網路上掀起了一陣討論，在馬來西亞和印尼的[決賽](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/29/malaysia-
indonesia-soccer-match-turns-into-war-of-words/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/29/malaysia-indonesia-soccer-match-
turns-into-war-of-
words/")時尤其熱烈。[柬埔寨](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/17/cambodia-
reactions-to-the-2010-world-cup-season/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/17/cambodia-reactions-to-
the-2010-world-cup-
season/")和[緬甸](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/04/myanmar-world-cup-
reactions/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/04/myanmar-world-cup-
reactions/")部落客對世界盃發表了一些有趣的評論。

**宗教**

[馬來西亞](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/13/church-attacks-in-malaysia/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/13/church-attacks-in-
malaysia/")和[印尼](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/19/indonesia-local-
government-closes-church-defying-court-order/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/19/indonesia-local-government-closes-
church-defying-court-
order/")的基督教教堂受到攻擊。[教會領袖](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/13/indonesia-
online-rage-over-attack-on-church-leaders/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/13/indonesia-online-rage-over-attack-
on-church-
leaders/")也被騷擾。柬埔寨[僧侶的品行](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/09/cambodia-
decline-of-monk-morality/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/09/cambodia-
decline-of-monk-
morality/")受到質疑。新加坡一名[牧師](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/21/singapore-
netizens-angry-over-pastor%E2%80%99s-comments-on-buddhism-and-taoism/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/21/singapore-netizens-angry-over-
pastor’s-comments-on-buddhism-and-
taoism/")嘲笑道教和佛教學說。汶萊部落客報導了穆斯林如何[慶祝](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/07/brunei-
charity-food-and-ramadhan/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/09/07/brunei-
charity-food-and-
ramadhan/")齋戒月。曼谷一間佛寺中發現超過兩千具[胎兒屍體](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/22/thailand-
two-thousand-dead-fetuses-in-buddhist-temple/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/22/thailand-two-thousand-dead-fetuses-
in-buddhist-temple/")，震驚泰國人民。

**教育**

菲律賓國立大學學生因[教育預算刪減](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/29/philippines-
student-unrest-over-education-budget-cuts/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/11/29/philippines-student-unrest-over-
education-budget-
cuts/")而發動罷課。將[性教育](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/07/philippines-
bloggers-views-on-sex-education/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/07/philippines-bloggers-views-on-sex-
education/")納入學校課程的提案也成了網路上的熱門話題。

馬來西亞實施了幾項教育改革，例如[取消](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/12/malaysia-
should-schools-abolish-examinations/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/12/malaysia-should-schools-abolish-
examinations/")兩項[初等學校](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/01/malaysia-
education-ministry-plans-to-scrap-two-exams/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/07/01/malaysia-education-ministry-plans-
to-scrap-two-
exams/")考試；最近則因為醫生與實習醫生過多而[凍結](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/14/malaysia-
moratorium-on-medical-schools/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/14/malaysia-moratorium-on-medical-
schools/")了醫學院的增招。

[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/06/pinkdot.jpg)](http://pinkdotsg.blogspot.com/2010/05/thank-
you-4000-of-you.html)

照片來自 Pink Dot 部落格

**性別**

菲律賓一個政治團體提案訂立[婚姻到期續約](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/26/philippines-%E2%80%9Crenewable-
marriage-bill%E2%80%9D/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/26/philippines-“renewable-marriage-
bill”/")法。新聞報導了馬來西亞的[兒童新娘](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/07/malaysias-14-year-
old-bride/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/12/07/malaysias-14-year-old-
bride/")問題。

柬埔寨第一個[女性入口網站](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/08/first-cambodian-
women-web-portal/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/08/first-cambodian-
women-web-
portal/")受到網路族群熱烈歡迎。[女性創業](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/12/indonesia-
when-women-control-their-own-investments/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/12/indonesia-when-women-control-their-
own-
investments/")在印尼受到越來越多的支持。汶萊部落客喚起大眾對[乳癌](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/26/brunei-
foodies-go-pink-2010/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/04/26/brunei-
foodies-go-pink-2010/")的重視。

新加坡的同性戀/雙性戀/跨性別社群成功舉辦了 Pink Dot
[活動](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/05/singapore-pink-dot-2010/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/05/singapore-pink-
dot-2010/")。柬埔寨部落客也公開談論[同性戀/雙性戀/跨性別議題](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/14/cambodia-
bloggers-discuss-lgbt-issues/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/01/14/cambodia-bloggers-discuss-lgbt-
issues/")。

馬來西亞三名婦女因[通姦](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/07/malaysia-3-women-
caned-for-having-illicit-sex/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/07/malaysia-3-women-caned-for-having-
illicit-
sex/")遭受鞭刑。有些團體形容菲律賓的「[跳舞的空服員](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/06/philippines-
dancing-flight-attendants/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/06/philippines-dancing-flight-
attendants/")」是性別歧視的噱頭。

**其他全球之聲報導**

菲律賓 2007 年的[跳舞的囚犯](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/29/philippines-
dancing-prisoners-tribute-to-michael-jackson/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/29/philippines-dancing-prisoners-
tribute-to-michael-jackson/")在 2010
年被[跳舞的稅務員](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/23/philippines-popular-
dancing-videos/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/23/philippines-
popular-dancing-
videos/")取代。在東南亞很受歡迎的[榴槤](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/28/southeast-
asia-durian-the-%E2%80%9Cking-of-fruits%E2%80%9D/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/28/southeast-asia-durian-the-“king-of-
fruits”/")是水果之王。該讓新加坡的美食部落客享用[免費餐點](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/27/singapore-
should-food-bloggers-get-free-meals/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/27/singapore-should-food-bloggers-get-
free-meals/")嗎？

許多人觀看了汶萊這段「[我很抱歉](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/20/brunei-im-sorry-
video-now-a-youtube-sensation/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/08/20/brunei-im-sorry-video-now-a-
youtube-
sensation/")」影片。印尼禁止[水牛](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/11/indonesia-
water-buffalo-banned-in-rallies/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/02/11/indonesia-water-buffalo-banned-in-
rallies/")參加競選活動。一名瑞士人在新加坡因為破壞公物而遭[鞭刑](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/30/singapore-
swiss-national-to-be-caned-for-train-vandalism/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/30/singapore-swiss-national-to-be-
caned-for-train-vandalism/")。

生產[棕櫚油](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/21/malaysia-whats-the-real-
deal-with-palm-oil/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/03/21/malaysia-whats-
the-real-deal-with-palm-
oil/")在馬來西亞引起的不只是能源問題。馬來西亞一座[監獄古蹟](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/27/malaysia-
historic-jail-demolished/ "https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/06/27/malaysia-
historic-jail-
demolished/")被拆除。柬埔寨允許人民在[自由公園](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/09/cambodia-
freedom-of-assembly-in-freedom-park/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/05/09/cambodia-freedom-of-assembly-in-
freedom-
park/")中抗議。河內慶祝建城[一千週年](https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/11/vietnam-
hanoi%E2%80%99s-1000th-birthday-festivities/
"https://globalvoicesonline.org/2010/10/11/vietnam-hanoi’s-1000th-birthday-
festivities/")。

在此僅代表全球之聲東南亞小組感謝各位讀者 2010 年的支持。我們在此承諾將繼續報導本地區突出的重要公民媒體事件。祝大家新年快樂！

